oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Southern States and Lime Corporation workers
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of several unidentified miners and Newton Duggins Walker Sr. (1880-1963), who was a partner and the general manager of the Southern States and Lime Corporation. Newton is leaning against a rock (on right) and watching the workers. A mule pulling a cart can be seen behind him.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Mine railroads; Miners; Mules
